detailedDescription.articleBody:
ASCII, abbreviated from American Standard Code for Information Interchange, is a character encoding standard for electronic communication. ASCII codes represent text in computers, telecommunications equipment, and other devices. Most modern character-encoding schemes are based on ASCII, although they support many additional characters.
The Internet Assigned Numbers Authority prefers the name US-ASCII for this character encoding.
ASCII is one of the IEEE milestones.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: एएससीआईआई, सूचना इंटरचेंज के लिए अमेरिकी मानक कोड से संक्षिप्त, इलेक्ट्रॉनिक संचार के लिए एक वर्ण एन्कोडिंग मानक है, एएससीआईआई कोड कंप्यूटर, दूरसंचार उपकरण और अन्य उपकरणों में पाठ का प्रतिनिधित्व करते हैं, अधिकांश आधुनिक चरित्र-एन्कोडिंग योजनाएं एएससीआईआई पर आधारित हैं, हालांकि वे कई अतिरिक्त का समर्थन करते हैं

detailedDescription.articleBody: Ascidiacea, commonly known as the ascidians, tunicates, and sea squirts, is a paraphyletic class in the subphylum Tunicata of sac-like marine invertebrate filter feeders.

detailedDescription.articleBody: AsciiDoc is a human-readable document format, semantically equivalent to DocBook XML, but using plain-text mark-up conventions.

detailedDescription.articleBody: Asciano is a comune and hill town in the province of Siena in the Italian region Tuscany. It is located at the centre of the Crete senesi between the river Ombrone and the torrent Copra, some 30 kilometres southeast of the town of Siena by rail.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: एसियानो इतालवी क्षेत्र टस्कनी में सिएना प्रांत में एक कम्यून और पहाड़ी शहर है, यह ओम्ब्रोन नदी और टोरेंट कोपरा के बीच क्रेते सेनेसी के केंद्र में स्थित है, जो रेल द्वारा सिएना शहर से लगभग 30 किलोमीटर दक्षिण-पूर्व में स्थित है।

detailedDescription.articleBody:
In computer programming, a null-terminated string is a character string stored as an array containing the characters and terminated with a null character. Alternative names are C string, which refers to the C programming language and ASCIIZ.
The length of a C string is found by searching for the NUL byte. This can be slow as it takes O(n) with respect to the string length. It also means that a string cannot contain a NUL character.
